args:
Their foes vanquished, Leif and Cecile unite
with the Sparrows. He invites her to join him at
the Halidom, but she declines, saying she
needs time to think on all that has transpired.
They then part with a promise to meet again.
Your cruel reign ends here, Harle!
Heh heh... And here I thought you were...\nsupposed to be the nice one. You didn't\neven hesitate to...
Consider it the kindness of a classmate\nthat I will dispatch you without suffering.
Heh heh heh... Aaaah ha ha ha!
He took a fatal blow and he's...laughing?
This? A fatal blow? Oh, please.
By the Goddess... His wound is closing!
I hadn't intended to use this power today...\nSeems I got...carried away in all the fun...
But sadly, our little game must end here.\nI cannot allow my grand design to be\nundone so close to its completion.
Not at the eve of my great master's advent!
Leif, no! That miasma is lethal!
Farewell for now, dear friends! I hope we\nare able to have another reunion someday!
What was that power? I've never seen\na person wield something like that...
(Harle always sought a world of equality.\nThat's why his fealty to the king was\nalways thin as onionskin.)
(So who would he choose to serve now?\nAnd what of that fell miasma?)
I am sorry to have worried you.
Not a problem, Captain. Now let's get\nacross the border before the hounds of\nGrams come after us!
And what will you do, Cecile?
Learning of your past hasn't changed my\nthoughts. Will you join us in New Alberia?
I understand both the guilt you carry\nand the regret it gives rise to.
And I hope you'll permit a friend to help\nyou shoulder that weight.
Do you need me to find you Manachew?
MMMMMEEEELTING! I'm melting in\nyour presence again, you damn blazing\nsun of a man!
Is that so? In that case, you'll just have to\nseek some shade, because Iâ€”
Because you're simply telling me what\nyour heart believes. Yes, I know.
And your words make me so incredibly\nhappy, but...

Well, this is just something I need to think
about for a whileâ€”on my own. I need to
understand exactly what being a knight
means to me now.
I failed to protect my king. I know this.
And even worse, I committed atrocities in\nhis name against innocent civilians and\ndragons both. None of that can change.
So now I need to find a new pathâ€”one\nthat doesn't lead me away from the past,\nbut takes me beyond it.
Plus, being at your side is...ummm...\nWell, it makes my heart feel like it's going\nto explode, and I'm not ready for that.
Or melt, maybe. Yeah, let's go with melt.\nIt's just too much direct sunlight.
It certainly would not do to have you\nmelt on me.
Well, if the two of us could fight alongside\neach other for Alberia again, I think...\nWell, I think that would be nice.
Then I shall wait for as long as I must.
Until you find your knightly path and we\ncan march into battle together once more.
Captain Leif? Who was that woman?
A former knight of Alberiaâ€”and an ally\nand friend to this day.
(I believe in you, Cecileâ€”and I know\nwe shall meet again.)
I can't exactly go back to Grams now,\nso look after the innkeep for me, yeah?
I'll get her back home safe and sound.
Thanks. Oh, and sorry for getting you two\nmixed up in my problems.
Oh, please. This wasn't your fault. Besides,\nit was worth it just to see you kick all that\nbutt up close!
Kick butt? I was a sobbing mess for a\ngood three-quarters of that!
Hush, child. I saw you fighting your heart\nout to keep us safe.
I've never seen a more impressive knight\nin all my days!
We'll be cheering you on from afar, dear.\nNow go give 'em hell!
I will. Be well, both of you.
(I never thought the day would come when\nI'd think about wanting to start over...)
ï¼‚Knight's Code, Article 10: A knight is a\nconduit for justice and good. Let iniquity\nand evil ever face your blade.ï¼‚
I don't know what my path will look like\nor where it will lead me, but I know one\nthing I'll never lose sight of again...
Justice remains alive inside of me.
